name: Fruiticana
address: Fruiticana, 6257 Fraser St, Vancouver, BC V5W 3A3

featured_reviews.review_id: Bought some frozen food from this store, The brand name was  Nilgiri, all 3 packets were spoiled and had fungus on the food, I called the store and informed the incident, they sounded like I was lying about it and said lot of other stores selling Nilgiri brands and demanded  receipt for refund, I had  no  plans to go back their  for a refund  as I live in surrey   and driving back  and forth will cost  me more in gas,my only intention was to report the incident,I recommend  to avoid this   store and Nilgiri products. I wasted my $24 in one day, never ever buy any NILGIRI frozen food, they sell poison.

featured_reviews.review_id: One of the larger Indian food stores on south Fraser Street and we always make a point to drop in here on our trips to this eclectic and vibrant neighbourhood! Lots of fruit and veg as well as packaged goods and foodstuffs from India and Pakistan. Extensive offering of spices, rice, frozen foods, bulk foods also. Typically busy especially on weekends! Mostly self serve as staff are always busy! Reasonable to good prices!

featured_reviews.review_id:
Fruiticana has almost all the groceries and home items you need as an Indian house hold!

It has fresh vegetables and frozen food options as well!

Only thing is isles spaces are too small, otherwise, everything us in order, you can remember place of items in your first visit only!

All the veggies are fresh in the morning and topped up every now and then. Even Chinese and Philippines origin also can be seen

featured_reviews.review_id: Typical Indian grocery store, with it's over crowding and somewhat unorganized shelves. That being said, it has most Desi items that you may need. The produce quality is good and prices reasonable. Staff is too busy at the counter but will help out if you plead long enough. If you live on the North shore, this is a must visit because we don't have anything like it. Parking is easier than expected behind the store and also on the adjacent street. Overall good place to find Indian items.

featured_reviews.review_id:
Good amount of Indian items available here ranging from veggies, fruits, snacks, whole grains, dairy and home essential.
Would recommend buying fruits and veggies from supermarket because at this place they may be cheap but not fresh sometimes. But great place for Frozen and packed Indian food items.

featured_reviews.review_id: I wish if I could rate this store in negative. I visited here july 10 aprox 8:30 means today. The cashier was very slow, she was not acting in a front house staff personality, was looking everyone very rudely like she don't want the customers to be there. When it came for my turn I paid the bill and was having my hand in the air for receipt but she just threw it on the counter like she was doing very everyone else. It was my last visit to the store and would make sure my message would be heard by all the customers and the appropriate authorities. Don't know if that employee was like that or they have this kind of standard for all employees but it was very bad experience.

featured_reviews.review_id: Bought this on 31st july 2022. I havent check the date or open the box in store. I have small kids at home he noticed it and told me that it is not good. The stuff inside is expired and have fungi on it. There is  no proper manufactured date on it. I called the worker  and she said just return it and get a new one. How hard is it to check manufacturers date of stuff before stacking it to aisle?
